Shortly before the start drivers had paid homage to Senna, the triple  world champion whose death has tended to overshadow that of rookie  Ratzenberger.
Gathered together at the front of the grid, where the first two places had  been left clear out of respect to the dead drivers, they made way for  Brazilians Christian Fittipaldi and Rubens Barichello, along with  Ratzenberger's German teammate Heinz Harald Frentzen, who all moved forward  with a Brazilian flag bearing the words "adeus Ayrton".
